A man was beheaded on Sunday evening in Kostot, West Pokot county after a quarrel during a drinking spree. Dickson Lipuul was killed during an argument with a youth at a local bar. Pokot Central deputy county commissioner Geoffrey Kithinji said the perpetrator escaped with Lipuul's head. "We are conducting investigations concerning what prompted the young man to be beheaded," he said. Kithinji also said police reservists are looking for the suspect.